As some fans might agree, the prequel trilogy of films was only made to lead up to the final scenes of this particular film.  For years, the rumor and stories of the birth of Vader were nearly legendary in their origins.  From the novelization of the original trilogy films was a reference to how Vader was so severely injured he must be encased in a suit which would breathe for him ... and ever since, fans have wanted to see this famous duel between Jedi Master Obi-Wan Kenobi and Dark Lord of the Sith Vader in a volcano.  Lucas has always said the novels are not really how he sees things, but are a nice way for fans to experience what isnÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢t on the screen.  So when Lucas took the fantastic story and expanded it from a single volcano to a planet of molten lava, fans rejoiced ...

Three years after the onset of the Clone Wars; the noble Jedi Knights are spread out across the galaxy leading a massive clone army in the war against the Separatists. After Chancellor Palpatine is kidnapped, Jedi Master Obi-Wan Kenobi and his former padawan, Anakin Skywalker, are dispatched to eliminate the evil General Grievous. Meanwhile, Anakin's friendship with the Chancellor arouses suspicion in the Jedi Order, and dangerous to the Jedi Knight himself. When the sinister Sith Lord, Darth Sidious, unveils a plot to take over the galaxy, the fate of Anakin, the Jedi order, and the entire galaxy is at stake. Upon his return, Anakin Skywalker learns his wife Padme Amidala is pregnant, but he is having visions of her dying in childbirth. Anakin Skywalker ultimately must choose between the Jedi and an alternative that may have the answers he so desperately needs to save his beloved wife.

